page.title: 09A DAY IN THE LIFE OF part 2
page.content: We took turns climbing the tree. We carried on. Peter saw some rabbits but I didn't. We walked quietly through a field of sheep by the old deserted house without any windows. Near Bumpit House we climbed over the fence & down the hill. We took some more photos then walked up the other hill. At last we were nearly home. We walked past Lynsted Church & opened our gate & walked up our garden path & went inside. I put my used film into an envelope to send off. I asked my dad for some lunch because my mum works in Sittingbourne library five days & sometimes six days a week so my dad normally gets lunch & supper ready. He also comes early from Christ Church College in Canterbury at about half past three or sometimes a bit later.
